<h5 id=3D"favoredEnemy">Favored Enemy (<a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/sr=
d/specialAbilities.htm#extraordinaryAbilities">Ex</a>)</h5>
<p>
	At 1st level, a ranger may select a type of creature from among those give=
n on <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/classes/ranger.htm#tableRangerFa=
voredEnemies">Table: Ranger Favored Enemies</a>. The ranger gains a +2 bonu=
s on <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/skills/bluff.htm">Bluff</a>, <a =
href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/skills/listen.htm">Listen</a>, <a href=
=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/skills/senseMotive.htm">Sense Motive</a>, <a=
 href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/skills/spot.htm">Spot</a>, and <a href=
=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/skills/survival.htm">Survival</a> checks whe=
n using these skills against creatures of this type. Likewise, he gets a +2=
 bonus on weapon damage rolls against such creatures.
</p>
<p>
	At 5th level and every five levels thereafter (10th, 15th, and 20th level)=
, the ranger may select an additional favored enemy from those given on the=
 table. In addition, at each such interval, the bonus against any one favor=
ed enemy (including the one just selected, if so desired) increases by 2.
</p>
<p>
	If the ranger chooses <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/typesSubtypes.=
htm#humanoidType">humanoids</a> or <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/ty=
pesSubtypes.htm#outsiderType">outsiders</a> as a favored enemy, he must als=
o choose an associated subtype, as indicated on the table. If a specific cr=
eature falls into more than one category of favored enemy, the ranger=E2=80=
=99s bonuses do not stack; he simply uses whichever bonus is higher.
</p>

<h5 id=3D"track">Track</h5>
<p>
	A ranger gains <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/feats.htm#track">Trac=
k</a> as a bonus feat.
</p>

<h5 id=3D"wildEmpathy">Wild Empathy (<a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/=
specialAbilities.htm#extraordinaryAbilities">Ex</a>)</h5>
<p>
	A ranger can improve the attitude of an animal. This ability functions jus=
t like a <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/skills/diplomacy.htm">Diplom=
acy</a> check to improve the attitude of a person. The ranger rolls 1d20 an=
d adds his ranger level and his Charisma modifier to determine the wild emp=
athy check result. The typical domestic animal has a starting attitude of i=
ndifferent, while wild animals are usually unfriendly.
</p>
<p>
	To use wild empathy, the ranger and the animal must be able to study each =
other, which means that they must be within 30 feet of one another under no=
rmal visibility conditions. Generally, influencing an animal in this way ta=
kes 1 minute, but, as with influencing people, it might take more or less t=
ime.
</p>
<p>
	The ranger can also use this ability to influence a <a href=3D"https://www=
.d20srd.org/srd/typesSubtypes.htm#magicalBeastType">magical beast</a> with =
an Intelligence score of 1 or 2, but he takes a -4 penalty on the check.
</p>

<h5 id=3D"combatStyle">Combat Style (<a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/=
specialAbilities.htm#extraordinaryAbilities">Ex</a>)</h5>
<p>
	At 2nd level, a ranger must select one of two combat styles to pursue: arc=
hery or two-weapon combat. This choice affects the character=E2=80=99s clas=
s features but does not restrict his selection of feats or special abilitie=
s in any way.
</p>
<p>
	If the ranger selects archery, he is treated as having the <a href=3D"http=
s://www.d20srd.org/srd/feats.htm#rapidShot">Rapid Shot</a> feat, even if he=
 does not have the normal prerequisites for that feat.
</p>
<p>
	If the ranger selects two-weapon combat, he is treated as having the <a hr=
ef=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/feats.htm#twoWeaponFighting">Two-Weapon Fi=
ghting</a> feat, even if he does not have the normal prerequisites for that=
 feat.
</p>
<p>
	The benefits of the ranger=E2=80=99s chosen style apply only when he wears=
 light or no armor. He loses all benefits of his combat style when wearing =
medium or heavy armor.
</p>

<h5 id=3D"endurance">Endurance</h5>
<p>
	A ranger gains <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/feats.htm#endurance">=
Endurance</a> as a bonus feat at 3rd level.
</p>

<h5 id=3D"animalCompanion">Animal Companion (<a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.=
org/srd/specialAbilities.htm#extraordinaryAbilities">Ex</a>)</h5>
<p>
	At 4th level, a ranger gains an animal companion selected from the followi=
ng list: <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/monsters/badger.htm">badger<=
/a>, <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/monsters/camel.htm">camel</a>, <=
a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/monsters/direRat.htm">dire rat</a>, <a=
 href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/monsters/dog.htm">dog</a>, <a href=3D"h=
ttps://www.d20srd.org/srd/monsters/dogRiding.htm">riding dog</a>, <a href=
=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/monsters/eagle.htm">eagle</a>, <a href=3D"ht=
tps://www.d20srd.org/srd/monsters/hawk.htm">hawk</a>, <a href=3D"https://ww=
w.d20srd.org/srd/monsters/horse.htm">horse</a> (light or heavy), <a href=3D=
"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/monsters/owl.htm">owl</a>, <a href=3D"https://w=
ww.d20srd.org/srd/monsters/pony.htm">pony</a>, <a href=3D"https://www.d20sr=
d.org/srd/monsters/snake.htm#viperSnake">snake</a> (Small or Medium viper),=
 or <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/monsters/wolf.htm">wolf</a>. If t=
he campaign takes place wholly or partly in an aquatic environment, the fol=
lowing creatures may be added to the ranger=E2=80=99s list of options: <a h=
ref=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/monsters/mantaRay.htm">manta ray</a>, <a =
href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/monsters/porpoise.htm">porpoise</a>, <a =
href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/monsters/shark.htm">Medium shark</a>, an=
d <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/monsters/squid.htm">squid</a>. This=
 animal is a loyal companion that accompanies the ranger on his adventures =
as appropriate for its kind.
</p>
<p>
	This ability functions like the <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/clas=
ses/druid.htm">druid</a> ability of the same name, except that the ranger=
=E2=80=99s effective druid level is one-half his ranger level. A ranger may=
 select from the alternative lists of animal companions just as a druid can=
, though again his effective druid level is half his ranger level. Like a d=
ruid, a ranger cannot select an alternative animal if the choice would redu=
ce his effective druid level below 1st.
</p>

<h5 id=3D"rangerSpells">Spells</h5>
<p>
	Beginning at 4th level, a ranger gains the ability to cast a small number =
of divine spells, which are drawn from the ranger spell list. A ranger must=
 choose and prepare his spells in advance (see below).
</p>
<p>
	To prepare or cast a spell, a ranger must have a Wisdom score equal to at =
least 10 + the spell level. The Difficulty Class for a <a href=3D"https://w=
ww.d20srd.org/srd/combat/combatStatistics.htm#savingThrows">saving throw</a=
> against a ranger=E2=80=99s spell is 10 + the spell level + the ranger=E2=
=80=99s Wisdom modifier.
</p>
<p>
	Like other spellcasters, a ranger can cast only a certain number of spells=
 of each spell level per day. His base daily spell allotment is given on <a=
 href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/classes/ranger.htm#tableTheRanger">Tabl=
e: The Ranger</a>. In addition, he receives bonus spells per day if he has =
a high Wisdom score. When <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/classes/ran=
ger.htm#tableTheRanger">Table: The Ranger</a> indicates that the ranger get=
s 0 spells per day of a given spell level, he gains only the bonus spells h=
e would be entitled to based on his Wisdom score for that spell level. The =
ranger does not have access to any <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/sp=
ellLists/clericDomains.htm">domain</a> spells or granted powers, as a <a hr=
ef=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/classes/cleric.htm">cleric</a> does.
</p>
<p>
	A ranger prepares and casts spells the way a <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd=
.org/srd/classes/cleric.htm">cleric</a> does, though he cannot lose a prepa=
red spell to cast a cure spell in its place. A ranger may prepare and cast =
any spell on the ranger spell list, provided that he can cast spells of tha=
t level, but he must choose which spells to prepare during his daily medita=
tion.
</p>
<p>
	Through 3rd level, a ranger has no caster level. At 4th level and higher, =
his caster level is one-half his ranger level.
</p>

<h5 id=3D"improvedCombatStyle">Improved Combat Style (<a href=3D"https://ww=
w.d20srd.org/srd/specialAbilities.htm#extraordinaryAbilities">Ex</a>)</h5>
<p>
	At 6th level, a ranger=E2=80=99s aptitude in his chosen combat style (arch=
ery or two-weapon combat) improves. If he selected archery at 2nd level, he=
 is treated as having the <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/feats.htm#m=
anyshot">Manyshot</a> feat, even if he does not have the normal prerequisit=
es for that feat.
</p>
<p>
	If the ranger selected two-weapon combat at 2nd level, he is treated as ha=
ving the <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/feats.htm#improvedTwoWeaponF=
ighting">Improved Two-Weapon Fighting</a> feat, even if he does not have th=
e normal prerequisites for that feat.
</p>
<p>
	As before, the benefits of the ranger=E2=80=99s chosen style apply only wh=
en he wears light or no armor. He loses all benefits of his combat style wh=
en wearing medium or heavy armor.
</p>

<h5 id=3D"woodlandStride">Woodland Stride (<a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.or=
g/srd/specialAbilities.htm#extraordinaryAbilities">Ex</a>)</h5>
<p>
	Starting at 7th level, a ranger may move through any sort of undergrowth (=
such as natural thorns, briars, overgrown areas, and similar terrain) at hi=
s normal speed and without taking damage or suffering any other impairment.
</p>
<p>
	However, thorns, briars, and overgrown areas that are enchanted or magical=
ly manipulated to impede motion still affect him.
</p>

<h5 id=3D"swiftTracker">Swift Tracker (<a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/sr=
d/specialAbilities.htm#extraordinaryAbilities">Ex</a>)</h5>
<p>
	Beginning at 8th level, a ranger can move at his normal speed while follow=
ing tracks without taking the normal -5 penalty. He takes only a -10 penalt=
y (instead of the normal -20) when moving at up to twice normal speed while=
 tracking.
</p>

<h5 id=3D"rangerEvasion">Evasion (<a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/spe=
cialAbilities.htm#extraordinaryAbilities">Ex</a>)</h5>
<p>
	At 9th level, a ranger can avoid even magical and unusual attacks with gre=
at agility. If he makes a successful <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/=
combat/combatStatistics.htm#reflex">Reflex saving throw</a> against an atta=
ck that normally deals half damage on a successful save, he instead takes n=
o damage. Evasion can be used only if the ranger is wearing light armor or =
no armor. A <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/conditionSummary.htm#help=
less">helpless</a> ranger does not gain the benefit of evasion.
</p>

<h5 id=3D"combatStyleMastery">Combat Style Mastery (<a href=3D"https://www.=
d20srd.org/srd/specialAbilities.htm#extraordinaryAbilities">Ex</a>)</h5>
<p>
	At 11th level, a ranger=E2=80=99s aptitude in his chosen combat style (arc=
hery or two-weapon combat) improves again. If he selected archery at 2nd le=
vel, he is treated as having the <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/feat=
s.htm#improvedPreciseShot">Improved Precise Shot</a> feat, even if he does =
not have the normal prerequisites for that feat.
</p>
<p>
	If the ranger selected two-weapon combat at 2nd level, he is treated as ha=
ving the <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/feats.htm#greaterTwoWeaponFi=
ghting">Greater Two-Weapon Fighting</a> feat, even if he does not have the =
normal prerequisites for that feat.
</p>
<p>
	As before, the benefits of the ranger=E2=80=99s chosen style apply only wh=
en he wears light or no armor. He loses all benefits of his combat style wh=
en wearing medium or heavy armor.
</p>

<h5 id=3D"camouflage">Camouflage (<a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/spe=
cialAbilities.htm#extraordinaryAbilities">Ex</a>)</h5>
<p>
	A ranger of 13th level or higher can use the <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd=
.org/srd/skills/hide.htm">Hide</a> skill in any sort of natural terrain, ev=
en if the terrain doesn=E2=80=99t grant <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/s=
rd/combat/combatModifiers.htm#cover">cover</a> or <a href=3D"https://www.d2=
0srd.org/srd/combat/combatModifiers.htm#concealment">concealment</a>.
</p>

<h5 id=3D"hideinPlainSight">Hide in Plain Sight (<a href=3D"https://www.d20=
srd.org/srd/specialAbilities.htm#extraordinaryAbilities">Ex</a>)</h5>
<p>
	While in any sort of natural terrain, a ranger of 17th level or higher can=
 use the <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/skills/hide.htm">Hide</a> sk=
ill even while being observed.
</p>

